How to sell a developer tool with 1M users
text:
Hi,

We are three developers and we have built a developer tool in our free time, This tool is a subset of Project management tools and mainly used by development teams. Long story short, during Covid it became very popular and still is Number 1 in organic search on Google. We have more than one million users from every company in the world you can think of.

The tool is based on a freemium model with most of the features available as free, and we have a paid tier as well. The tool is used heavily with 180000-220000 users sessions and around 15000 new signups every month. We have spent zero amount on marketing and have not spent any efforts on sales etc.

All the growth is organic and word of mouth marketing. We believe there for the people with sales and marketing skills there is huge potential to either make it a real business with a very good MRR or it can be a good strategic investment for any big player like MIRO, Monday or click up etc. Where they can acquire Million users from large enterprises and then use their sales teams to generate revenue out of it.

Now we are looking for some advice on how to approach those large players and negotiate with them etc. What is the standard process in Silicon Valley around this, we are based in Europe and would like to get some advice, input or potential contacts etc.

Thanks in advance!

Ask HN: What Chrome Extensions are you using currently?
text:
I am looking to improve my extensions foo.

You can get this list easily by evaluating the following js after visiting the url chrome://extensions

  copy(document.querySelector('extensions-manager').extensions_.map(({id, name, state, webStoreUrl}) => (name)))
Mine are:- [ "Bypass Paywalls", "Sci-Hub", "Fakespot Fake Amazon Reviews and eBay Sellers", "GitHub User Languages", "GMass: Powerful mail merge for Gmail", "Google Analytics Debugger", "Google Docs Offline", "Hacker News discussion", "Old Reddit Redirect", "React Developer Tools", "Redux DevTools", "Refined GitHub", "Refined Hacker News", "removeddit", "SponsorBlock for YouTube - Skip Sponsorships", "Toggle JavaScript", "uBlock Origin", "Vue.js devtools", "What Hacker News Says", ]

Ask HN: Funding? Seeking Funding?
text:
Please lead with either SEEKING INVESTMENT or INVESTING, with your location.

If you are seeking investments, please give a short overview of the types of projects you are interested in funding, and how much money you'd like to invest in a given project.

If you are seeking funding, please give a short overview of your business, how much you're trying to raise, how much equity you're offering, and what you plan to use the capital for.

Please be respectful of others' email inboxes.

title: Weird Google Browser Signature
text:

the IP reverse lookup is from googleusercontent.com 137.22.142.34.bc.googleusercontent.com
